The paper deals with the group testing problem, which is a well-studied problem in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The measures studied in the paper, $c_{\cal M}(d)$ and $c_{\cal M}$, are related to combinatorics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of randomized algorithms and probability theory suggests a possible connection to statistical inference (cs.SI).
